What is N-Butyl Acetate?
N-Butyl Acetate is a clear, colorless liquid with a pleasant fruity odor, widely used as an industrial solvent due to its excellent solvency power, controlled evaporation rate, and compatibility with numerous resins and polymers. It is produced through the esterification of n-butyl alcohol and acetic acid using sulfuric acid as a catalyst.

Modern industrial applications of N-Butyl Acetate include:

·         High-performance solvent for paints, coatings, and lacquers

·         Solvent for synthetic resins, natural gums, and adhesives

·         Chemical intermediate for plastics, artificial pearls, and safety glass

·         Pharmaceutical solvent for extraction and formulation processes

·         Fragrance carrier in perfumes and cosmetics

·         Industrial cleaning and specialty chemical applications

By delivering excellent solvency, smooth coating performance, and reliable evaporation characteristics, N-Butyl Acetate remains one of the most widely used industrial solvents across coatings, chemicals, pharmaceuticals, automotive, and manufacturing industries.

